repo_track_justification: Repository on GitHub, which uses git. git can track the changes, who made them, and when they were made.
repo_interim_justification:
We are releasing daily builds from the main development branch. Installation instructions are here: https://kubevirt.io/user-guide/operations/installation/#installing-the-daily-developer-builds
Before each stable release which occurs monthly we are also releasing release candidates, where the final rc gets promoted to the release if it passes the requirements. Our release process is described here: https://github.com/kubevirt/kubevirt/blob/master/docs/release.md#cadence-and-timeline
For our stable releases we use GitHub: https://github.com/kubevirt/kubevirt/releases
repo_distributed_justification: Repository on GitHub, which uses git. git is distributed.
version_tags_justification: We have github releases which are based on signed git tags: https://github.com/kubevirt/kubevirt/releases
release_notes_justification:
We have a published version in our user-guide available here: https://kubevirt.io/user-guide/latest_release_notes/
Also https://github.com/kubevirt/kubevirt/releases contains all our releases with release notes attached.
vulnerability_report_response_justificat: no vulnerabilities reported in the last 6 months: https://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvekey.cgi?keyword=KubeVirt
test_justification: We have an e2e test suite under: https://github.com/kubevirt/kubevirt/tree/master/tests and unit tests can be run via `make test` or simply `go test ./...`.
test_invocation_justification: Unit tests can be run via `make test` or simply `go test ./...`.
test_most_justification: Our unit-test code-coverage is roughtly 60% at the moment, so not perfect, but we have in addition e2e tests which cover any feature we support.
test_policy_justification: Every new feature requires unit- and functional tests to be accepted.
tests_documented_added_justification: We have a paragraph in our contribution document: https://github.com/kubevirt/kubevirt/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#testing
warnings_justification: We run https://github.com/bazelbuild/rules_go/blob/master/go/nogo.rst on our code-base, which uses a bunch of go tools for quality checking, inglucing `vet`.
warnings_fixed_justification: We only merge go code where `vet` succeeded.
warnings_strict_justification: We only merge go code where `vet` succeeded.
know_secure_design_justification:
https://github.com/kubevirt/kubevirt/commits?author=davidvossel
https://github.com/kubevirt/kubevirt/commits?author=rmohr

Both have extensive experience in that field and are the main contributors.
know_common_errors_justification:
https://github.com/kubevirt/kubevirt/commits?author=davidvossel
https://github.com/kubevirt/kubevirt/commits?author=rmohr

Both have extensive experience in that field and are the main contributors.
crypto_published_justification: We use TLS and authentication mechanisms on top of it (oauth, ...). There we mostly just integrate with existing authentication and authorization systems, as provided by k8s itself.
crypto_call_justification: We use golangs built-in tls libraries.
crypto_floss_justification: We use golangs built-in tls libraries which are FLOSS compatible.
crypto_working_justification: We only use tls in a sane configuration.
crypto_pfs_justification: We only use tls in a sane configuration.
delivery_mitm_justification: We secure all connections via TLS.
delivery_unsigned_justification: We secure all connections via TLS.
static_analysis_common_vulnerabilities_j: We fix anything which go vet reports.
static_analysis_fixed_justification: Runs on every commit, nothing is merged without passing.
static_analysis_often_justification: Runs on every commit, nothing is merged without passing.
dynamic_analysis_justification: We have a broad suite of unit and integration tests, also we use Sonarcloud as a quality gate. We are currently investigating in how to integrate fuzz testing into our build and release workflow.
crypto_weaknesses_justification: We only use tls in a sane configuration.
test_continuous_integration_justificatio: We have our own tide instance: https://prow.apps.ovirt.org/. We use in the repo automated merges via tide, which ensures the we only merge non-broken code.
discussion_justification: GitHub supports discussions on issues and pull requests.
no_leaked_credentials_justification: There are some credentials in the repo, but they are encrypted and can only be decrypted by travis.
